OL,7,FDuring his trial, opinion pieces he
OL,8,Fwrote for his newspaper, the Apple
OL,9,FDaily, and his contact with US
OL,10,Fpoliticians, including the former Vice
OL,11,FPresident Mike Pence, were used to
OL,12,Fsupport charges that he colluded with
OL,13,Fforeign forces and published seditious
OL,14,Fmaterial.
OL,16,FAfter his arrest, his newspaper
OL,17,Foffices were raided and closed, a day
OL,18,Fwhich Human Rights Watch described as
OL,19,Fthe end of free speech in Hong Kong.
